content.webTitle: Pick of the Week: South: Clubbing

fields.headline: Pick of the Week: Clubs
fields.bodyText: Eric Prydz Syndicate, Bristol, Saturday 25 Apr The Call On Me-reworking king of Euro cheese-trance plugs in for a session of electro-housery. Storm 9th Birthday Emporium, Coalville, Saturday 25 Apr Most clubs count themselves lucky to make nine weeks, let alone nine years, so three parps on the horn of longevity to this trance, house and techno favourite. Action Aid Presents 6º Live ICA, London, Wednesday 29 Apr It's rare that you get to campaign for women's rights in the developing world and party to thecocknbullkid and Micachu, but tonight is that night. Annie Mac Presents KOKO, London, Thursday 30 Apr The superstar DJ brings her mates to London, and what a list of mates it is: Little Boots, the Count & Sinden, Toddla T and Plan B all make an appearance. Annie Mac Presents Komedia, Brighton, Friday 1 May There's a strict "no cheese" policy in place here, so expect a far classier blend of Philly soul, Blaxploitation, 70s Motown and Afrobeat.
